article_node.title: Google Parent Alphabet Helps Lead Rebound On Wall Street
article_node.summary: Alphabet shares surged 8.5% after a judge ruled it need not divest Chrome or Android, lifting the Nasdaq and S&P 500 by about 1% and 0.4% respectively, while the Dow fell 0.3%. The rally was supported by softer U.S. labor market data, boosting expectations of a Fed rate cut, and by strong gold stocks, though oil prices fell, weighing on energy equities.
